      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a political scientist at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.essex.ac.uk/departments/government&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Essex&lt;/a&gt; and I am affiliated with the &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.sas.upenn.edu/pic-lab/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Identity &amp;amp; Conflict Lab&lt;/a&gt; at the University of Pennsylvania. I have previously held positions at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://socialsciences.exeter.ac.uk/politics/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Exeter&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.uni-wh.de/en/uwh-international/university/faculty-of-management-and-economics/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Witten/Herdecke&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.essex.ac.uk/people/borma58507/nils-christian-bormann&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;research&lt;/a&gt; I investigate why political elites in ethnically divided societies decide to cooperate rather than fight one another, how economic inequality between ethnic groups develops over time, and what effects international intervention has on the stability of ethnic power sharing.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
